      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SODA SNOOP (8) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where he gave a sight, finishing third (22.47) and beaten 9 lengths over 390m at Shepparton. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Rates highly and will give a great sight. LONE TORNADO (1) was game in defeat at the latest run, finishing third and beaten 1.75 lengths (19.22) behind Magic I Am at this track. Expected to feature again. RUN BINDI RUN (2) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 330m at this track, taking a Grade 5 in a strong 18.82. Smart winner two back and looks a key chance on that form. JACOBITE THORN (3) is a last-start placegetter here at this trip - worth considering.",
